    <title>Tesla Cybertuck recalled again, this time over faulty wiper and trim</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="Photo illustration of a Tesla Cybertruck." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xmjf6LC1s3FmR6VKi61vKKLRhUo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73426124/236937_Cybertruck_CVirginia.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Cybertruck is suffering from real-world issues. &lt;/em&gt; | The Verge / Photo by Bloomberg, Getty Images&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="hV6sk7"&gt;Tesla is again issuing a physical recall of its Cybertruck. This time it’s recalling 11,688 of its electric pickups due to &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/17/24180519/tesla-cybertruck-deliveries-windshield-wiper-issue"&gt;a faulty windshield wiper&lt;/a&gt; that could reduce visibility for the driver, and 11,383 Cybertrucks due to trim in the truck bed that could come loose and create a road hazard for others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="s8Wn96"&gt;These new recalls follow a recall in April affecting &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/19/24134753/tesla-recall-cybertruck-faulty-accelerator-pedal-nhtsa-defect"&gt;3,878 Cybertrucks over the risk of a jammed accelerator pedal&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="ilC4jb"&gt;Issues with the gigantic wiper had &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/17/24180519/tesla-cybertruck-deliveries-windshield-wiper-issue"&gt;surfaced in owner forums&lt;/a&gt; in recent weeks and reportedly delayed Cybertruck deliveries on short notice. &lt;a href="https://static.nhtsa.gov/odi/rcl/2024/RCLRPT-24V456-3775.PDF"&gt;The NHTSA recall notice&lt;/a&gt; for the wiper says that “excessive electrical current can cause the front windshield wiper motor controller to fail.” Tesla service will replace the wiper motor,...&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;
